# Release-Gate

**This file is yours.** `rasa.module.releases` ships the portable release
lifecycle (`.claude/release-rules.md` + the `/release` skills), but it
deliberately does not decide the two things that vary per project:

1. **What makes a release shippable** — which checks must be green, and
2. **How this project actually deploys** — the deploy command + tag model.

This file is where you define both. `/release` reads it at pre-flight and
hard-stops if a required check fails or the deploy command is missing.

A release is cut only when **every readiness check below passes** and the
**deploy command runs clean**. Each check must be **objectively
checkable** — a command that exits zero, a named approval — never a
feeling. Never bypass a check to ship faster.

---

## Readiness checks (EDIT THIS)

> Replace the defaults with your project's real checks. Until you do, the
> minimum honest bar applies: a clean tree, a green test command, and a
> human sign-off. Running on the default is a smell, not a destination.

- [ ] **Clean tree** — `git status --porcelain` is empty.
- [ ] **Tests green** — `<your test command>` exits 0.
- [ ] **Build clean** — `<your build command>` exits 0 (warnings fatal? y/n).
- [ ] **Dependency audit** — `<your audit command>` shows no new HIGH/CRITICAL.
- [ ] **Approval** — the release closer has reviewed and approved.

---

## Deploy command (EDIT THIS — REQUIRED)

> `/release` hard-stops if this is unset. Guessing prod commands is the
> one inference the skill refuses to make.

```sh
# How this project ships to production. One of:
#
#   # (a) delegate to the pipelines module, if mounted:
#   bash build/stages/50-deploy.sh --env prod
#
#   # (b) a raw project command:
#   npm run deploy            # web
#   fastlane release          # ios
#   ./deploy.sh prod          # bespoke
#
DEPLOY_CMD="<fill me in>"
```

## Tag model (EDIT THIS)

```sh
# Plain semver is the default:
TAG="vX.Y.Z"
#
# To stamp the commit + environment into the tag, define a helper that
# emits e.g. v1.2.0-9f3a1c7-prod. If the pipelines module is mounted, use
# its environment helper; otherwise:
# TAG="vX.Y.Z-$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)-prod"
```

## Rollback command (EDIT THIS)

```sh
# Reverts the live build. Does NOT move git tags (see release-rules.md →
# Rollback semantics). Example:
#   firebase hosting:rollback
ROLLBACK_CMD="<fill me in>"
```

