## Examples — delete the ones you don't need

> Pick the block that matches your stack, paste it above, and tune it.

### Web (Firebase / Vercel / static)

```markdown
- [ ] Tests — `npm test` exits 0.
- [ ] Build — `npm run build` clean (warnings fatal).
- [ ] Audit — `npm audit --audit-level=high` clean.
DEPLOY_CMD="npm run deploy:prod"
ROLLBACK_CMD="firebase hosting:rollback"
```

### iOS (Xcode / fastlane)

```markdown
- [ ] Tests — `xcodebuild test -scheme App` exits 0.
- [ ] Build — `xcodebuild -scheme App -config Release` clean.
DEPLOY_CMD="fastlane release"
TAG="vX.Y.Z-$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)-appstore"
```

### Container / Kubernetes

```markdown
- [ ] Tests — `make test` exits 0.
- [ ] Image — `tests/container/greenlight.sh` passes (validate + run-local).
DEPLOY_CMD="bash build/stages/50-deploy.sh --env prod"   # pipelines module
ROLLBACK_CMD="kubectl rollout undo deploy/<app>"
```

---

## Note on co-mounted modules

If `rasa.module.pipelines` is mounted, prefer pointing `DEPLOY_CMD` at its
deploy stage rather than duplicating the command here — one source of
truth for "how we ship." If `rasa.module.tests` is mounted, your "tests
green" check can run a named suite (`tests/suites/prod-gate.md`) instead
of a raw command.
